view(landings)
landings <- landings %>%
  subset(select = -c(...7:...34)) %>%
  rename(year = YEAR) %>%
  rename(port = "PORT NAME") %>%
  rename(state = STATE) %>%
  rename(sp_name = SPPNAME) %>%
  rename(landed_lbs = "LANDED LBS") %>%
  rename(live_lbs = "LIVE LBS")
landings <- landings %>%
  filter(year >= 1995)
landings$landed_lbs <- gsub(",", "", landings$landed_lbs)
landings$landed_lbs <- as.integer(landings$landed_lbs)

landings$live_lbs <- gsub(",", "", landings$live_lbs)
landings$live_lbs <- as.integer(landings$live_lbs)

str(landings)
## tibble [75,129  6] (S3: tbl_df/tbl/data.frame)
##  $ year      : num [1:75129] 1995 1996 1997 1998 1999 ...
##  $ port      : chr [1:75129] "CONFIDENTIAL" "CONFIDENTIAL" "CONFIDENTIAL" "CONFIDENTIAL" ...
##  $ state     : chr [1:75129] "CO" "CO" "CO" "CO" ...
##  $ sp_name   : chr [1:75129] "CONFIDENTIAL" "CONFIDENTIAL" "CONFIDENTIAL" "CONFIDENTIAL" ...
##  $ landed_lbs: int [1:75129] 16742061 19097133 17774064 16771298 19135245 18972047 9930 31212 1540 4898 ...
##  $ live_lbs  : int [1:75129] 70239231 85067279 61897420 50668748 54343035 61017170 9930 34351 12822 4898 ...
lobster_landings <- landings %>%
  filter(sp_name == "LOBSTER, AMERICAN") %>%
  group_by(year, state) %>%
  summarise(lobster_lbs = sum(landed_lbs))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
total_landings <- landings %>%
  group_by(year, state) %>%
  summarise(total_lbs = sum(landed_lbs))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
lobster_landings %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = lobster_lbs, color = state)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(
    title = "Landed Pounds of American Lobster in New England, 1995-2021",
    x = "Year",
    y = "Landed Pounds",
    color = "State"
  )

lobster_landings <- lobster_landings %>%
  select(year, state, lobster_lbs) %>%
  group_by(state) %>%
  mutate(previous_year = lag(lobster_lbs, order_by = year)) %>%
  view()

lobster_landings %>%
  mutate(pChange = ((lobster_lbs - previous_year)/lobster_lbs * 100)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = pChange, color = state)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(
    title = "Landed Pounds of American Lobster in New England, 1995-2021",
    x = "Year",
    y = "Landed Pounds",
    color = "State"
  )
